{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"I want to say that really and truly,"},{"time":2000,"text":"after these incredible speeches"},{"time":4000,"text":"and ideas that are being spread,"},{"time":6000,"text":"I am in the awkward position"},{"time":8000,"text":"of being here to talk to you today"},{"time":10000,"text":"about television."},{"time":13000,"text":"So most everyone watches TV."},{"time":15000,"text":"We like it. We like some parts of it."},{"time":18000,"text":"Here in America, people actually love TV."},{"time":21000,"text":"The average American watches TV"},{"time":24000,"text":"for almost 5 hours a day."},{"time":27000,"text":"Okay?"},{"time":29000,"text":"Now I happen to make my living these days in television,"},{"time":32000,"text":"so for me, that's a good thing."},{"time":34000,"text":"But a lot of people don't love it so much."},{"time":37000,"text":"They, in fact, berate it."},{"time":39000,"text":"They call it stupid,"},{"time":41000,"text":"and worse, believe me."},{"time":43000,"text":"My mother, growing up,"},{"time":45000,"text":"she called it the \"idiot box.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":47000,"text":"But my idea today is not to debate"},{"time":49000,"text":"whether there's such a thing as good TV or bad TV;"},{"time":52000,"text":"my idea today"},{"time":54000,"text":"is to tell you that I believe"},{"time":56000,"text":"television has a conscience."},{"time":59000,"text":"So why I believe that television has a conscience"},{"time":62000,"text":"is that I actually believe"},{"time":64000,"text":"that television directly reflects"},{"time":67000,"text":"the moral, political,"},{"time":69000,"text":"social and emotional need states of our nation --"},{"time":72000,"text":"that television is how we actually disseminate"},{"time":75000,"text":"our entire value system."},{"time":77000,"text":"So all these things are uniquely human,"},{"time":80000,"text":"and they all add up"},{"time":82000,"text":"to our idea of conscience."}]},{"cues":[{"time":84000,"text":"Now today, we're not talking about good and bad TV."},{"time":86000,"text":"We're talking about popular TV."},{"time":89000,"text":"We're talking about top-10 Nielsen-rated shows"},{"time":92000,"text":"over the course of 50 years."},{"time":94000,"text":"How do these Nielsen ratings"},{"time":96000,"text":"reflect not just what you've heard about,"},{"time":99000,"text":"which is the idea of our social, collective unconscious,"},{"time":103000,"text":"but how do these top-10 Nielsen-rated shows"},{"time":105000,"text":"over 50 years"},{"time":107000,"text":"reflect the idea"},{"time":109000,"text":"of our social conscience?"},{"time":111000,"text":"How does television evolve over time,"},{"time":113000,"text":"and what does this say about our society?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":115000,"text":"Now speaking of evolution,"},{"time":117000,"text":"from basic biology, you probably remember"},{"time":120000,"text":"that the animal kingdom, including humans,"},{"time":123000,"text":"have four basic primal instincts."},{"time":125000,"text":"You have hunger; you have sex; you have power;"},{"time":128000,"text":"and you have the urge for acquisitiveness."},{"time":132000,"text":"As humans, what's important to remember"},{"time":134000,"text":"is that we've developed, we've evolved over time"},{"time":137000,"text":"to temper, or tame,"},{"time":139000,"text":"these basic animal instincts."},{"time":142000,"text":"We have the capacity to laugh and cry."},{"time":145000,"text":"We feel awe, we feel pity."},{"time":147000,"text":"That is separate and apart"},{"time":149000,"text":"from the animal kingdom."},{"time":151000,"text":"The other thing about human beings"},{"time":153000,"text":"is that we love to be entertained."},{"time":156000,"text":"We love to watch TV."},{"time":158000,"text":"This is something that clearly separates us"},{"time":160000,"text":"from the animal kingdom."},{"time":162000,"text":"Animals might love to play,"},{"time":164000,"text":"but they don't love to watch."}]},{"cues":[{"time":167000,"text":"So I had an ambition"},{"time":169000,"text":"to discover what could be understood"},{"time":171000,"text":"from this uniquely human relationship"},{"time":173000,"text":"between television programs"},{"time":175000,"text":"and the human conscious."},{"time":177000,"text":"Why has television entertainment evolved the way it has?"},{"time":180000,"text":"I kind of think of it"},{"time":182000,"text":"as this cartoon devil or angel"},{"time":184000,"text":"sitting on our shoulders."},{"time":186000,"text":"Is television literally functioning"},{"time":188000,"text":"as our conscience,"},{"time":190000,"text":"tempting us and rewarding us at the same time?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":193000,"text":"So to begin to answer these questions,"},{"time":195000,"text":"we did a research study."},{"time":197000,"text":"We went back 50 years"},{"time":199000,"text":"to the 1959/1960 television season."},{"time":202000,"text":"We surveyed the top-20 Nielsen shows"},{"time":204000,"text":"every year for 50 years --"},{"time":206000,"text":"a thousand shows."},{"time":208000,"text":"We talked to over 3,000 individuals --"},{"time":210000,"text":"almost 3,600 --"},{"time":212000,"text":"aged 18 to 70,"},{"time":214000,"text":"and we asked them how they felt emotionally."},{"time":216000,"text":"How did you feel"},{"time":218000,"text":"watching every single one of these shows?"},{"time":221000,"text":"Did you feel a sense of moral ambiguity?"},{"time":223000,"text":"Did you feel outrage? Did you laugh?"},{"time":226000,"text":"What did this mean for you?"},{"time":228000,"text":"So to our global TED audiences,"},{"time":230000,"text":"I want to say that this was a U.S. sample."},{"time":232000,"text":"But as you can see,"},{"time":234000,"text":"these emotional need states are truly universal."},{"time":237000,"text":"And on a factual basis,"},{"time":239000,"text":"over 80 percent of the U.S.'s most popular shows"},{"time":242000,"text":"are exported around the world."},{"time":244000,"text":"So I really hope our global audiences"},{"time":246000,"text":"can relate."}]},{"cues":[{"time":248000,"text":"Two acknowledgments"},{"time":250000,"text":"before our first data slide:"},{"time":252000,"text":"For inspiring me"},{"time":254000,"text":"to even think about the idea of conscience"},{"time":257000,"text":"and the tricks that conscience can play on us on a daily basis,"},{"time":261000,"text":"I thank legendary rabbi, Jack Stern."},{"time":265000,"text":"And for the way in which I'm going to present the data,"},{"time":268000,"text":"I want to thank TED community superstar Hans Rosling,"},{"time":271000,"text":"who you may have just seen."}]},{"cues":[{"time":273000,"text":"Okay, here we go."},{"time":275000,"text":"So here you see,"},{"time":277000,"text":"from 1960 to 2010,"},{"time":279000,"text":"the 50 years of our study."},{"time":282000,"text":"Two things we're going to start with --"},{"time":284000,"text":"the inspiration state and the moral ambiguity state,"},{"time":287000,"text":"which, for this purpose,"},{"time":289000,"text":"we defined inspiration"},{"time":291000,"text":"as television shows that uplift me,"},{"time":293000,"text":"that make me feel much more positive about the world."},{"time":296000,"text":"Moral ambiguity are televisions shows"},{"time":299000,"text":"in which I don't understand"},{"time":301000,"text":"the difference between right and wrong."},{"time":304000,"text":"As we start, you see in 1960"},{"time":306000,"text":"inspiration is holding steady."},{"time":308000,"text":"That's what we're watching TV for."},{"time":310000,"text":"Moral ambiguity starts to climb."},{"time":312000,"text":"Right at the end of the 60s,"},{"time":314000,"text":"moral ambiguity is going up,"},{"time":316000,"text":"inspiration is kind of on the wane."},{"time":318000,"text":"Why?"},{"time":320000,"text":"The Cuban Missile Crisis, JFK is shot,"},{"time":322000,"text":"the Civil Rights movement,"},{"time":324000,"text":"race riots, the Vietnam War,"},{"time":326000,"text":"MLK is shot, Bobby Kennedy is shot,"},{"time":328000,"text":"Watergate."},{"time":330000,"text":"Look what happens."},{"time":332000,"text":"In 1970, inspiration plummets."},{"time":334000,"text":"Moral ambiguity takes off."},{"time":336000,"text":"They cross,"},{"time":338000,"text":"but Ronald Reagan, a telegenic president, is in office."},{"time":340000,"text":"It's trying to recover."},{"time":342000,"text":"But look, it can't:"},{"time":344000,"text":"AIDS, Iran-Contra,"},{"time":346000,"text":"the Challenger disaster, Chernobyl."},{"time":348000,"text":"Moral ambiguity becomes the dominant meme in television"},{"time":352000,"text":"from 1990 for the next 20 years."}]},{"cues":[{"time":354000,"text":"Take a look at this."},{"time":356000,"text":"This chart is going to document a very similar trend."},{"time":359000,"text":"But in this case, we have comfort -- the bubble in red --"},{"time":362000,"text":"social commentary and irreverence"},{"time":364000,"text":"in blue and green."},{"time":367000,"text":"Now this time on TV"},{"time":369000,"text":"you have \"Bonanza,\" don't forget, you have \"Gunsmoke,\""},{"time":372000,"text":"you have \"Andy Griffith,\""},{"time":374000,"text":"you have domestic shows all about comfort."},{"time":377000,"text":"This is rising. Comfort stays whole."},{"time":380000,"text":"Irreverence starts to rise."},{"time":382000,"text":"Social commentary is all of a sudden spiking up."},{"time":385000,"text":"You get to 1969, and look what happens."},{"time":388000,"text":"You have comfort, irreverence, and social commentary,"},{"time":391000,"text":"not only battling it out in our society,"},{"time":394000,"text":"but you literally have two establishment shows --"},{"time":398000,"text":"\"Gunsmoke\" and \"Gomer Pyle\" --"},{"time":400000,"text":"in 1969 are the number-two- and number-three-rated television shows."},{"time":403000,"text":"What's number one?"},{"time":405000,"text":"The socially irreverent hippie show,"},{"time":408000,"text":"\"Rowan and Martin's Laugh-In.\""},{"time":410000,"text":"They're all living together, right."},{"time":412000,"text":"Viewers had responded dramatically."}]},{"cues":[{"time":414000,"text":"Look at this green spike in 1966"},{"time":417000,"text":"to a bellwether show."},{"time":419000,"text":"When you guys hear this industry term, a breakout hit,"},{"time":421000,"text":"what does that mean?"},{"time":423000,"text":"It means in the 1966 television season,"},{"time":426000,"text":"The \"Smothers Brothers\" came out of nowhere."},{"time":430000,"text":"This was the first show"},{"time":432000,"text":"that allowed viewers to say,"},{"time":434000,"text":"\"My God,"},{"time":436000,"text":"I can comment on how I feel about the Vietnam War,"},{"time":439000,"text":"about the presidency, through television?\""},{"time":441000,"text":"That's what we mean by a breakout show."}]},{"cues":[{"time":444000,"text":"So then, just like the last chart, look what happens."},{"time":447000,"text":"In 1970,"},{"time":449000,"text":"the dam bursts. The dam bursts."},{"time":451000,"text":"Comfort is no longer why we watch television."},{"time":454000,"text":"Social commentary and irreverence"},{"time":456000,"text":"rise throughout the 70s."},{"time":458000,"text":"Now look at this."},{"time":460000,"text":"The 70s means who? Norman Lear."},{"time":463000,"text":"You have \"All in the Family,\" \"Sanford and Son,\""},{"time":465000,"text":"and the dominant show --"},{"time":467000,"text":"in the top-10 for the entire 70s --"},{"time":469000,"text":"\"M<i>A</i>S*H.\""},{"time":471000,"text":"In the entire 50 years"},{"time":473000,"text":"of television that we studied,"},{"time":476000,"text":"seven of 10 shows"},{"time":479000,"text":"ranked most highly for irreverence"},{"time":482000,"text":"appeared on air during the Vietnam War,"},{"time":484000,"text":"five of the top-10 during the Nixon administration."},{"time":488000,"text":"Only one generation, 20 years in,"},{"time":491000,"text":"and we discovered,"},{"time":493000,"text":"Wow! TV can do that?"},{"time":496000,"text":"It can make me feel this?"},{"time":498000,"text":"It can change us?"},{"time":501000,"text":"So to this very, very savvy crowd,"},{"time":503000,"text":"I also want to note"},{"time":506000,"text":"the digital folks did not invent disruptive."},{"time":509000,"text":"Archie Bunker was shoved out of his easy chair"},{"time":511000,"text":"along with the rest of us"},{"time":513000,"text":"40 years ago."}]},{"cues":[{"time":515000,"text":"This is a quick chart. Here's another attribute:"},{"time":517000,"text":"fantasy and imagination,"},{"time":519000,"text":"which are shows defined as,"},{"time":521000,"text":"\"takes me out of my everyday realm\""},{"time":524000,"text":"and \"makes me feel better.\""},{"time":526000,"text":"That's mapped against the red dot, unemployment,"},{"time":528000,"text":"which is a simple Bureau of Labor Department statistic."},{"time":532000,"text":"You'll see"},{"time":534000,"text":"that every time fantasy and imagination shows rise,"},{"time":537000,"text":"it maps to a spike in unemployment."},{"time":540000,"text":"Do we want to see shows"},{"time":542000,"text":"about people saving money and being unemployed?"},{"time":545000,"text":"No. In the 70s"},{"time":547000,"text":"you have the bellwether show \"The Bionic Woman\""},{"time":550000,"text":"that rocketed into the top-10 in 1973,"},{"time":553000,"text":"followed by the \"Six Million-Dollar Man\" and \"Charlie's Angels.\""},{"time":556000,"text":"Another spike in the 1980s --"},{"time":559000,"text":"another spike in shows about control and power."},{"time":563000,"text":"What were those shows?"},{"time":565000,"text":"Glamorous and rich."},{"time":567000,"text":"\"Dallas,\" \"Fantasy Island.\""},{"time":570000,"text":"Incredible mapping of our national psyche"},{"time":573000,"text":"with some hard and fast facts:"},{"time":575000,"text":"unemployment."}]},{"cues":[{"time":578000,"text":"So here you are, in my favorite chart,"},{"time":581000,"text":"because this is our last 20 years."},{"time":583000,"text":"Whether or not you're in my business,"},{"time":585000,"text":"you have surely heard or read"},{"time":588000,"text":"of the decline of the thing called the three-camera sitcom"},{"time":591000,"text":"and the rise of reality TV."},{"time":595000,"text":"Well, as we say in the business,"},{"time":597000,"text":"X marks the spot."},{"time":599000,"text":"The 90s -- the big bubbles of humor --"},{"time":601000,"text":"we're watching \"Friends,\" \"Frasier,\" \"Cheers\" and \"Seinfeld.\""},{"time":604000,"text":"Everything's good, low unemployment."},{"time":607000,"text":"But look: X marks the spot."},{"time":610000,"text":"In 2001,"},{"time":612000,"text":"the September 2001 television season,"},{"time":615000,"text":"humor succumbs to judgment once and for all."},{"time":619000,"text":"Why not?"},{"time":621000,"text":"We had a 2000 presidential election"},{"time":623000,"text":"decided by the Supreme Court."},{"time":625000,"text":"We had the bursting of the tech bubble."},{"time":627000,"text":"We had 9/11."},{"time":629000,"text":"Anthrax becomes part of the social lexicon."},{"time":632000,"text":"Look what happens when we keep going."},{"time":634000,"text":"At the turn of the century, the Internet takes off,"},{"time":637000,"text":"reality television has taken hold."},{"time":640000,"text":"What do people want in their TV then?"},{"time":642000,"text":"I would have thought revenge"},{"time":645000,"text":"or nostalgia."},{"time":647000,"text":"Give me some comfort; my world is falling apart."},{"time":649000,"text":"No, they want judgment."},{"time":651000,"text":"I can vote you off the island."},{"time":653000,"text":"I can keep Sarah Palin's daughter dancing."},{"time":656000,"text":"I can choose the next American Idol. You're fired."},{"time":659000,"text":"That's all great, right?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":662000,"text":"So as dramatically different as these television shows,"},{"time":666000,"text":"pure entertainment, have been over the last 50 years --"},{"time":669000,"text":"what did I start with? --"},{"time":671000,"text":"one basic instinct remains."},{"time":673000,"text":"We're animals, we need our moms."},{"time":676000,"text":"There has not been a decade of television"},{"time":678000,"text":"without a definitive, dominant TV mom."},{"time":682000,"text":"The 1950s:"},{"time":684000,"text":"June Cleever in the original comfort show, \"Leave it to Beaver.\""},{"time":687000,"text":"Lucille Ball kept us laughing"},{"time":690000,"text":"through the rise of social consciousness in the 60s."},{"time":693000,"text":"Maude Findlay,"},{"time":695000,"text":"the epitome of the irreverent 1970s,"},{"time":698000,"text":"who tackled abortion, divorce,"},{"time":700000,"text":"even menopause on TV."},{"time":702000,"text":"The 1980s,"},{"time":704000,"text":"our first cougar was given to us"},{"time":707000,"text":"in the form of Alexis Carrington."},{"time":710000,"text":"Murphy Brown took on a vice president"},{"time":712000,"text":"when she took on the idea of single parenthood."},{"time":717000,"text":"This era's mom,"},{"time":719000,"text":"Bree Van de Kamp."},{"time":722000,"text":"Now I don't know if this is the devil or the angel"},{"time":725000,"text":"sitting on our conscience,"},{"time":727000,"text":"sitting on television's shoulders,"},{"time":729000,"text":"but I do know that I absolutely love this image."}]},{"cues":[{"time":734000,"text":"So to you all,"},{"time":736000,"text":"the women of TEDWomen, the men of TEDWomen,"},{"time":738000,"text":"the global audiences of TEDWomen,"},{"time":741000,"text":"thank you for letting me present my idea"},{"time":743000,"text":"about the conscience of television."},{"time":745000,"text":"But let me also thank the incredible creators"},{"time":748000,"text":"who get up everyday"},{"time":750000,"text":"to put their ideas on our television screens"},{"time":753000,"text":"throughout all these ages of television."},{"time":755000,"text":"They give it life on television, for sure,"},{"time":758000,"text":"but it's you as viewers,"},{"time":760000,"text":"through your collective social consciences,"},{"time":763000,"text":"that give it life, longevity,"},{"time":765000,"text":"power or not."}]},{"cues":[{"time":767000,"text":"So thanks very much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":769000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}